<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="417" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1504,1783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1504,1530]" pageId="8" pageNumber="417">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Samaai &amp; Kelly" authorityYear="2002" box="[282,421,1504,1530]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Tsitsikamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="417" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[282,421,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="417">Tsitsikamma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species that are thickly encrusting to hemispherical attached to the substratum through a common base; have a rigid, thick honeycomb chamber like choanosome reinforced by very large, thick anisostyles. The isochiadiscorhabd microscleres are large, having a thick shaft and three sets of cylindrical-conical tubercles protruding from the shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="417" type="discussion">
